metadata.name: Growth v02 #403
metadata.description:
Growth patterns, version 2. January 2022
Edition of 512

Growth v02 is an generative exploration of patterns in the style of William Morris' iconic wallpaper designs from the 1800s. The code for the Growth series was originally designed to create plausible road networks but has been rewritten to create more organic curved forms. Created with p5js.

'space' to pause the simulation
'h' to toggle to higher res (increases canvas size but runs slower: great for screengrabs)
'r' to reset the seed (some features are locked to the original hash)
's' to save an image to disk
All generated patterns are tile-able horizontally and vertically.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

This project relies heavily on randomly generated values. It has been thoroughly tested. However, there is always the chance that the wrong combination of randomness can create less-compelling growth. If you feel you version is not living up to the potential promised with this piece, please email me.

metadata.name: A Forgotten Landscape #1
CMYK (Death of a Medium) #126
metadata.description:
Four colors have the capacity to make up the entire spectrum of printed work. Here on the digital screen, their purpose is destroyed. Cyan, magenta, yellow, and black are enlarged, torn apart, and blended back together to form something new. 

Build up each color in turn using the left and right arrows. 
Bring all colors back with the return key.
Separate each color from its neighbor with the up arrow.
Align each color accurately with the down arrow.
Reset the initial state of each color with the delete key.
Press the space bar to show and hide the derived image.

metadata.name: Kink #125
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you’d like to receive a physical plot!

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Sector J #8
metadata.description:
I have always been fascinated by large apartment complexes at night. For this piece, I'm trying to convey the feeling of being just one anonymous person surrounded by thousands of people we don't know. 

The owner of each token gets assigned a random room that will be the only white one among all the others in the sector.

Features are:
- Color: 8 traits
- Moon Size: 3 traits
- Building Density: 3 traits
- Smog Level: 4 traits

Households and Population are calculated based the actual real number of apartment units in the sector.

Room number is accurate and based on room number standards in Japan. It is composed of the floor number and the room number on that floor. Please note that the ground floor is floor 1.

Each building has multiple traits: height, width, floors, rooms by floor, antenna, entrance door.

Each room has multiple traits: rounded, curtains, blinders, lamp, frame, fence, light on or off.

Press ‘enter’ to skip the introduction.
Press ‘s’ to save an image.
Press ‘f’ to toggle fullscreen.

metadata.name: hash cats – genesis #72
metadata.description:
Mono was your typical countryside cat. During one late-night prowl, Mono discovered The Hash. All the other cats were astonished by the beauty of the thrilling find. Not before long did all the cats find themself living in the vibrant New Hash City. To keep up with the constant adrenaline rush of their new life, the cats have developed several traits to help them master the city.

hash cats are a group of 512 generated cats with numerous different features.

Rarity features include:
– 9 head colors
– 32 different head-gears
– 46 collars
– 40 upper face traits (eyewear and makeup)
– 3 lower face traits
– 15 mouth and nose types
– 46 sweaters and hoodies
– 81 sweater traits
– 3 gaze directions
– 29 background patterns * 30 swatch variations
– A very small chance to mint a cat with an artist signature

~ 1% chance to mint a Mono cat

hash cats is a collaboration GENTK by @levoontin & @3amkind.

Type 's' to save a PNG image of your cat (in full screen).

 → Follow @hash_cats_ on Twitter for updates on the cats!

metadata.name: Pine trees in the cold #11
metadata.description:
Pine and cypress trees were originally trees growing in cold zones and mountains. Due to their long-term life in cold environment, they have formed a unique cold resistant structure. The leaves of pine and cypress trees are generally reduced in needle shape, linear or scale shape. Due to the small leaf area, water is not easy to evaporate and lose. Some leaves have thick cutin or wax, and some have thick villi. If you take a pine needle and observe it carefully, you can see that there are dense white fluff on it, which feels very smooth when touching,

This is the picture of pine and cypress in the cold winter
